parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the headlights can cause a significant safety risk, especially at night, as it can leave the driver without visibility, increasing the likelihood of accidents.
symptoms: The headlights turn off or dim while driving
often returning to normal operation after switching the headlights off and on again. The issue can affect one or both headlights
and may occur randomly
making it difficult to predict when it will happen.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator can cause the loss of power-assisted braking, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop in a timely manner
the ABS light and brake warning light illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to skid or lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle skids or loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake fluid accumulator can cause the loss of power-assisted braking, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop in a timely manner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel can cause the driver to be unaware of the vehicle's speed, fuel level, and other essential information, leading to safety risks.
symptoms: The instrument panel display is blank or not functioning
making it difficult to monitor speed
fuel level
and other vital information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights turn off intermittently or do not turn on at all
reducing visibility while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard to press
or the vehicle takes longer to stop
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the odometer can cause issues with maintenance and inspection, potentially leading to safety risks.
symptoms: The odometer is stuck or not functioning
making it difficult to track mileage and perform necessary maintenance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The electrical system fails
causing issues with the clock
airbag
horn
and cruise control.
